The paper deals with unsupervised probabilistic modeling for discovering aspects and sentiments from text, which is a common theme in natural language processing and machine learning. The paper also focuses on incorporating attributes explicitly, which is relevant to topics such as information retrieval and recommendation systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
